President Muhammadu Buhari has narrated how he escaped being bombed near the Kawo bridge in Kaduna State while travelling to Katsina State in July 2014.Buhari disclosed this while commissioning the newly constructed Kawo bridge executed by the Kaduna State government on Thursday. He said, “There was an attempt to bomb me here…there was a market nearby but my security escort were vigilant.”The Kawo bridge was a project, many said had become a cynosure, which had attracted many tourists to Kaduna since its completion.Other projects commissioned by the President included the ultra modern sports and shopping complex at Murtala Square Kaduna, where he reiterated the likelihood of his staying in Kaduna after leaving office.